Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project following the official documentation.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
- Updated package.json to include the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with the resolved dependencies

### 2. Code Changes
Modified: `app/layout.tsx`
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag of the root layout
- Preserved all existing code structure, metadata, fonts, and styling

### 3. Implementation Details
- Followed the Next.js App Router integration pattern from official Vercel documentation
- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body tag as recommended
- No configuration changes needed - the component works out of the box

### 4. Verification
- Build completed successfully with no errors
- Linting passed for the modified layout.tsx file
- TypeScript compilation successful
- No breaking changes introduced

## What This Enables:
Once deployed to Vercel, this will automatically track:
- Page views and visits
- User engagement metrics
- Web Vitals (Core Web Vitals)
- Custom events (when configured)

## Next Steps (Manual):
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the changes to production
3. Verify analytics tracking by checking the Network tab for requests to the analytics endpoint
4. Configure custom events if needed for specific tracking requirements

The implementation follows Vercel's best practices and is ready for production deployment.
